22/03/2004
TBILISI, Georgia -- Parliament Speaker Nino Burjanadze met with Turkish Parliamentary EU Adjustment Commission Chairman Yasar Yakis on Saturday (20 March) to discuss bilateral co-operation and possible confidence-building measures regarding the Ajaria province conflicts. Yakis said that Turkey values Georgia's territorial integrity and is willing to support confidence-building measures, but would not send troops to the region. He met with Georgian President Mikhail Saakashvili and Prime Minister Zurab Zhvania earlier on Saturday, discussing ways to increase bilateral co-operation and enhance security and stability in the region. (Anadolu Agency, NTV - 21/03/04)
